.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-waitlist - Join the BCDock waitlist


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock waitlist [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Join the BCDock waitlist.

.PP
BCDock is in early access. Submit a waitlist entry and an admin reviews it, then
emails you an invite code (typically within 48 hours). Once you have the code,
run 'bcdock auth signup'.

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  1   general error
  4   rate-limited


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for waitlist


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock waitlist join --name "Jane Smith" --email jane@example.com
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock(1)\fP, \fBbcdock-waitlist-join(1)\fP
